Former England international footballer David Beckham arrives at Bromley Magistrates Court in Bromley, south-east of London on May 9, 2019, where his case of driving whilst using a mobile phone is being held. LONDON - Former England footballer David Beckham was on Thursday disqualified from driving for six months for using his phone while behind the wheel. READ: Beckham admits using phone while driving, police say The 44-year-old admitted the offence after being spotted by a member of the public as he drove his Bentley in London in November. He pleaded guilty and was also given six points on his licence.